headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored a season-high 30 points and made three free throws in the final minute to break a tie and help the surging Toronto Raptors beat the Indiana Pacers 107-102 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby's hot hand helps short-handed Raptors beat Pacers

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 34 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat Oklahoma City 108-101 on Sunday for their seventh consecutive victory and second straight over the Thunder.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Thunder 108-101, tie for NBA's best record

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 20 of his 33 points in the third quarter and the Boston Celtics snapped their three-game losing streak Sunday night by cruising to a 141-103 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 33, leads Celtics to 141-103 win over Cavs

headlines.description: — Gordon Hayward broke a tie with a layup with 0.7 seconds left and scored 39 points in the Charlotte Hornets' 107-104 comeback victory over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayward breaks late tie, scores 39 points to lead Hornets

events.name: Washington Wizards at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Patty Mills scored 21 points, Lonnie Walker IV added 16 and the San Antonio Spurs used their depth to beat Washington 121-101 on Sunday night in the Wizards' first game in two weeks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards fall to Spurs 121-101 in return from COVID-19 layoff

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 27 points and 14 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Atlanta Hawks 129-115 on Sunday night to snap a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 27 points, Bucks beat Hawks, 129-115

events.name: New York Knicks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 39 points, including six 3-pointers, and the rested Portland Trail Blazers jumped out early against the New York Knicks on the way to a 116-113 victory on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard leads rested Trail Blazers past Knicks 116-113
